81.6	Gamma_correction	Gamma correction	Gamma correction, gamma nonlinearity, gamma encoding, or often simply gamma, is the name of a nonlinear operation used to code and decode luminance or tristimulus values in video or still image systems. Gamma correction is, in the simplest cases, defined by the following power-law expression:	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/GammaFunctionGraph.svg/220px-GammaFunctionGraph.svg.png
